(226, 1, '2013-09-12 01:49:41', '2013-09-12 01:49:41', 'The social media company announced late Monday it is buying MoPub, a mobile-focused advertising exchange, in its fourth major purchase of the year.\n\nTerms of the deal were not disclosed. Published reports put the price at about $300 million or more, based an estimated values of Twitter''s<a href="http://money.cnn.com/2013/07/10/investing/twitter-fund-trading/index.html?iid=EL">privately-held stock</a> that is being used to make the purchase.\nTwitter''s statement said that MoPub''s technology lets mobile application publishers manage their inventory of multiple sources of advertising.', 'multimedia powerhouse', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'multimedia-powerhouse', '', '', '2013-09-12 01:49:41', '2013-09-12 01:49:41', '', 0, 'http://wenak.org/flatbox/?post_type=portfolio-items&amp;p=226', 0, 'portfolio-items', '', 0),
(232, 1, '2013-09-12 01:54:37', '2013-09-12 01:54:37', '"A Business Insider <strong>executive</strong> has made some comments on Twitter that do not reflect our values and have no place at our company. The executive has left the company, effective immediately," he stated.\n\n[alert type="success"]\n<h2>Twitter is on a <em>#buyingspree</em></h2>\n[/alert]\n\nThis historic <strong>passageway</strong> was once worn into a dense chain of dusty trails by caravans of horses and camels carrying merchants and their many wares between continental Asia and Europe.\n<blockquote>Today it takes the form of a series of transnational rail tracks transporting the latest in electronic products and computer parts.</blockquote>', ' The Industry Tech', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-industry-tech', '', '', '2013-09-12 01:54:37', '2013-09-12 01:54:37', '', 0, 'http://wenak.org/flatbox/?post_type=portfolio-items&amp;p=232', 0, 'portfolio-items', '', 0),
(242, 1, '2013-09-12 02:02:32', '2013-09-12 02:02:32', 'The social media company announced late Monday it is buying <strong>MoPub</strong>, a mobile-focused advertising exchange, in its fourth major purchase of the year.\n<div id="ie_column">\n<div id="quigo220">\n<div id="ad-121f148185b65ec8" align="center"><iframe id="121f148185b65ec8" name="121f148185b65ec8" src="http://ads.cnn.com/html.ng/site=cnn_money&amp;cnn_money_position=220x200_ctr&amp;cnn_money_rollup=technology&amp;cnn_money_section=quigo&amp;params.styles=fs&amp;page.allowcompete=no&amp;Params.User.UserID=522fb75e0652470aa5147703c263fef9&amp;transactionID=13789517993253016064950272&amp;tile=2497081598731&amp;domId=121f148185b65ec8&amp;kxid=&amp;kxseg=" height="0" width="0" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n</div>\nTerms of the deal were not disclosed. Published reports put the price at about $300 million or more, based an estimated values of Twitter''s<a href="http://money.cnn.com/2013/07/10/investing/twitter-fund-trading/index.html?iid=EL">privately-held stock</a> that is being used to make the purchase.\nTwitter''s statement said that MoPub''s technology lets mobile application publishers manage their inventory of multiple sources of advertising.\n\n<a href="http://money.cnn.com/2013/05/31/technology/social/twitter-users/index.html?iid=EL">Related: Twitter''s identity crisis</a>\n\nTwitter, which is believed to be weighing an <a href="http://money.cnn.com/2013/02/28/technology/twiter-ipo.pr.fortune/index.html?iid=EL">initial public offering</a> some time in 2014, has been buying a number of tech startups as it tries to <a href="http://tech.fortune.cnn.com/2013/04/17/can-twitter-become-a-multimedia-powerhouse/?iid=EL">transform itself</a> into more of a multimedia hub.', 'Business Insider', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'business-insider', '', '', '2013-09-12 02:02:32', '2013-09-12 02:02:32', '', 0, 'http://wenak.org/flatbox/?post_type=portfolio-items&amp;p=242', 0, 'portfolio-items', '', 0),
